Other high-risk frontliners like police and teachers should then be considered for prioritisation depending on their deployment status.Our vaccination strategy must aim at protecting those at greatest risk of death, in our case those aged 60 years and above. As we approach the end of this truly terrible year in recent human history due to the Covid-19 pandemic, there are multiple rays of hope that we must nurture and harness in the coming year.
Several pharmaceutical companies have now produced and tested vaccines that are on track to receive emergency use authorisation in many parts of the world.



