The challenge now for our government is to start thinking strategically about distribution and use of these vaccines.
However, there have been worries about our ability to store and transport these vaccines, and these must be quickly dispensed with. Firstly, several hospitals and research labs in this country have the capacity to store the vaccines at temperatures as low as -80 degrees centigrade.
Secondly, newer vaccines have been developed that do not require such low temperatures and can be stored in the same equipment currently being used in most hospitals to store other vaccines and medication requiring refrigeration.



