The challenge of storage is, therefore, surmountable and should not bother us too much at this point.
The more pertinent question is whether the government has identified a vaccine suitable for our population, and whether sufficient thinking has gone into the amount of resources required to procure sufficient quantities to protect our population.
Covid vaccines
Further, we must ask whether we have thought through the criteria we will use to prioritise vaccine recipients in the inevitable event that the quantities procured are limited.
We cannot depend on strategies developed in high-income countries that have different population structures and priorities. In Kenya, a Covid-19 vaccine strategy must be more customised.



